# Assignment brief (Sea Ice 2026)

**Research question:** Has the day-of-year of the Arctic sea ice area annual minimum shifted over the satellite era?

- **(a)** Has the minimum shifted earlier or later?
- **(b)** Why it matters: An earlier minimum means a longer melt season and more albedo feedback — directly relevant to Prof. Notz's CO₂–sea ice work.
- **(c)** What you did: Daily Arctic SIA (OSI SAF / UHH-compatible lineage), day-of-year of annual minimum per year, linear trend + significance.
- **(d)** Result: One plot — day-of-year of SIA minimum vs. year, trend line, confidence interval.

## One-pager structure

| Section | Content |
